  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Benson Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Proverbs 3:30-32",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Proverbs 3:30-32",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Strive not — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Either by words before the magistrate, or otherwise by thine actions; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "with a man without cause — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Without just and necessary cause; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "if he have done thee no harm — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Whereby it is clearly implied, that, in case of injury, a man may, by all lawful means, defend himself. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Envy thou not the oppressor — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "For his impunity and success in his wicked designs, and the wealth which he gains by unrighteous practices; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "and choose none of his ways — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "For what men envy in others they seek to obtain for themselves. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "For the froward — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Or, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "perverse, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "who walks in crooked and sinful paths, as the oppressor last mentioned, opposed to the upright man, who is called ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "right, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "or ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "straight, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Proverbs 29:27",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "is an abomination to the Lord — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And therefore, sooner or later, must be miserable. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "But his secret is with the righteous — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "They are his friends and favourites, to whom he familiarly imparts, as men use to do to their friends, his mind and counsels, or his secret favours and comforts, to which other men are strangers.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Matthew Henry's Concise Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "3:27-35 Our business is to observe the precepts of Christ, and to copy his example; to do justice, to love mercy, and to beware of covetousness; to be ready for every good work, avoiding needless strife, and bearing evils, if possible, rather than seeking redress by law. It will be found there is little got by striving. Let us not envy prosperous oppressors; far be it from the disciples of Christ to choose any of their ways. These truths may be despised by the covetous and luxurious, but everlasting contempt will be the portion of such scorners, while Divine favour is shown to the humble believer.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
